President Donald Trump has proclaimed May 1, 2020, as Law Day in the United States. In his proclamation, he highlights the importance of the rule of law and the unique framework of the American government, which secures individual liberties and protects against arbitrary exercise of government power. He emphasizes the need for the government to control itself and the importance of separate and coequal branches sharing power. President Trump also recognizes the 150th anniversary of the ratification of the 15th Amendment and the 100th anniversary of the ratification of the 19th Amendment, which granted voting rights to people of color and women respectively. He urges Americans to honor and defend the principles of the rule of law, limited government, and individual liberty.